iStock Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Benghazi - Rival militias have clashed in neighbourhoods across the Libyan capital of Tripoli, and the state-run Lana news agency says at least eight militiamen have been killed.The clashes sent tanks and convoys of armed militiamen streaming into the streets.The sides are split between rival militias vying for control of the city: One has its origins in Tripoli, while the other side is led by forces originally from the western city of Misrata and has Islamist leanings.Pictures posted on social media showed masked armed men on pick-up trucks in the streets in Tripoli.Libya sank into lawlessness and divisions after the downfall of the longtime leader Muammar Gaddafi in 2011.24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.